HEADWORD: Straddling
<hw>Strad"dling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Applied to spokes
when they are arranged alternately in two circles in the hub. See
<er>Straddle</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos>, and <er>Straddle</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos>, 3.</def> <rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

